  "prompt": "Is there an Android application that I can use to lookup words anywhere on my phone, without needing to have the application opened?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several Android applications that allow you to look up words without having to open the app directly. These apps typically float over other applications or provide quick access features. Here are some options:\n\n1. **Google Translate**: It offers a \"Tap to Translate\" feature that allows you to translate text from any app by copying it to the clipboard. Although primarily a translation tool, it can effectively be used as a dictionary for many languages.\n\n2. **Instant Dictionary by GoodWy**: This app offers a floating button that can be used to look up words from any app. When you select a word and tap the floating button, it provides definitions and synonyms.\n\n3. **Copy Dictionary**: This app enables word lookup by copying the desired word to the clipboard. It detects the copy action and shows the definition in a popup.\n\n4. **LookUp**: While mainly known for its beautiful interface, LookUp may have features like quick search from notifications or widgets that facilitate easy access from anywhere on your phone.\n\n5. **Any soft keyboard dictionaries**: Some third-party keyboards offer built-in dictionaries or plug-ins that provide word definitions or suggestions directly from the keyboard interface.\n\nAlways ensure you check app permissions and privacy policies to ensure they meet your security and privacy requirements.",
